pypebbles
-------------------------------------------
A board is filled with stones of different colors. Your goal is to make 
lines of stones of the same color. Two neighbouring stones can swap 
places, but only if a line of three or more stones is formed that way. 
Those lines will then disappear, letting other stones fall down. You 
score points for every line that disappears. It's that simple!

Runtime requirements:
  python-2.5.1-1
  python-pygame-1.7.1-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://pypebbles.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/pypebbles/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack pypebbles-0.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pypebbles-0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pypebbles-0.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pypebbles-0.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/pypebbles
